<html tal:replace="structure container/manage_page_header"/>

  <div tal:omit-tag="" tal:define="now python: DateTime()">

    <span tal:replace="structure here/manage_tabs"/>

  <br/>
 
  <form action="" tal:attributes="action request/URL1" method="post">
     <table cellpadding="2" width="100%">
       <tr>
           <td class="form-optional">Source</td>
           <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/getObjectFSPath"/>
       </tr>
       <tr>
           <td align="left" valign="top" class="form-label">Customize</td>
           <td align="left" valign="top" class="form-element">
            <em>Select a destination folder and press the button
            to make a copy of this script that can be customized.</em><br>
            <select name="folder_path" size="1">
                <option tal:repeat="path python: here.listCustFolderPaths('ZScheduleEvent')" 
                        tal:content="path"/>
             </select>
             <input type="submit" name="manage_doCustomize:method" value=" Customize ">
           </td>
        </tr>
        <tr tal:define="ob python: getattr(container, here.callable_id)"
             tal:condition="python: here.callable_id != here.id">
            <td class="form-label">Callable</td> 
            <td class="form-element">
                <img src="" tal:attributes="src string:${request/BASEPATH1}/${ob/icon}">&nbsp;
                <a href="" tal:attributes="href string:${ob/absolute_url}/manage_main" 
                           tal:content="ob/getId"/>&nbsp;&nbsp;
                <span tal:replace="ob/title"/>
            </td>
         </tr>
         <tr><td class="form-label">Title</td>
             <td class="form-element" colspan="2" tal:content="here/title"/>
         </tr>
         <tr><td class="form-label">Timezone</td>
             <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/tz"/>
         </tr>
      <TR>
	<TD class="form-label" ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">Execute At</TD>
	<TD ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2" class="form-element" nowrap
            tal:content="here/nextEventTime" />
      </TR>
      <TR>
	<TD class="form-label" ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP">Now is</TD>
        <TD class="form-element" nowrap 
            tal:content="python: now.toZone(here.tz)"/>
      </TR>
       <tr><td colspan="2" class="form-help">
             <br>
             <p>The following time specification fields all expect to be comprised of numbers
                from within the range specified.  Unix users may note that the 
                time specifications are fully compliant with the crontab utility, meaning you
                may combine any of the following to create very granular intervals:</p>
              <table border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2">
                   <tr class="list-item">
                     <td class="form-label">&nbsp;</td>
                     <td class="form-label">Feature</td>
                     <td class="form-label">Symbol</td>
                     <td class="form-label">Example</td>
                     <td class="form-label">Indicates</td>
                   </tr>
                   <tr class="list-item">
                      <td>&nbsp;</td>
                      <td>Ranges</td>
                      <td class="form-label" align="center">-</td>
                      <td>1-4</td>
                      <td><em>1,2,3,4</em></td>
                   </tr>
                   <tr class="list-item">
                      <td>&nbsp;</td>
                      <td>Explicit Values</td>
                      <td class="form-label" align="center">,</td>
                      <td>1,2,12</td>
                      <td><em>1,2,12</em></td>
                   </tr>
                   <tr class="list-item">
                      <td>&nbsp;</td>
                      <td>Increments</td>
                      <td class="form-label" align="center">/</td>
                      <td>0-12/3</td>
                      <td><em>0,3,6,9,12</em></td>
                   </tr>
             </table>
             <p>The wildcard, <em>*</em> means to include all possible values for this 
                parameter. You cannot set both the Day of Month value and the Day of 
                Week Value.</p>
             <br>
          </td>
         </tr>
         <tr><td class="form-optional">Minute</td>
              <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/minute"/>
         </tr>
         <tr>
                <td class="form-optional">Hour</td>
                <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/hour"/>
         </tr>
         <tr>
                <td class="form-optional">Month</td>
                <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/month"/>
         </tr>
         <tr>
                <td class="form-optional" nowrap>Day of Month</td>
                <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/day_of_month"/>
         </tr>
         <tr>
                <td class="form-optional" nowrap>Day of Week</td>
                <td class="form-element" tal:content="here/day_of_week"/>
         </tr>
    </table>

    </form>

  </div>
<html tal:replace="structure container/manage_page_footer"/>

